ame of this bird commemorates the American naturalist Frederick Albion Ober. Taxonomy The Montserrat oriole was formally described in 1880 by the American amateur ornithologist George Newbold Lawrence from a specimen collected on the island Montserrat during an expedition to the West Indies led by the US naturalist Frederick Albion Ober. Lawrence introduced the current binomial name Icterus oberi, with the specific epithet chosen to honour Ober. The genus Icterus was introduced by the French zoologist Mathurin Jacques Brisson in 1760. The species is monotypic: no subspecies are recognised. References External links BirdLife Species Factsheet.", "shortSummary": "The Montserrat oriole (Icterus oberi) is a medium-sized black-and-yellow icterid (the same family as many blackbirds, meadowlarks, cowbirds…", "locations": ["Centre Hills", "South Soufriere Hills", "重点鸟区", "蒙特塞拉特", "西印度群岛"], "threats": ["栖息地破坏"], "lat": 16.75, "lng": -62.20611111, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b5/Icterus_oberi.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-icterus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-icterus-oberi", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-icterus", "species": "taxonomy-species-icterus-oberi"}, "expandable": true, "x": -157.6, "y": 347.03, "z": 158.42}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-icterus", "name": "Icterus", "latinName": "Icterus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Icterus（Icterus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联29种鸟类，如Hispaniolan oriole、Cuban oriole、Bahama oriole等29种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 29, "x": -401.37, "y": 42.53, "z": -38.19}], "links": [{"key": "bird-montserrat-oriole-fd9add92__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-icterus-oberi", "source": "bird-montserrat-oriole-fd9add92", "target": "taxonomy-species-icterus-o